vtail, a graphical 'tail -f' like utility, with highlighting capabilities.

To display the usage:
 vtail --help

To use:
 vtail [options] [file]

If file is not supplied, the standard input will be used.
In additions to individual options, you can supply a file containing one option
per line, using the @ symbol (see the etc directory for examples.)

For instance, to use with adb (Android debug bridge):
 adb -d logcat -v time | vtail @/path/to/vtail/etc/logcat.ini
